      "id": "1444096265066512604",
      "type": "Reply",
      "timestamp": "2025-11-28T22:42:59.603+00:00",
      "timestampEdited": null,
      "callEndedTimestamp": null,
      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "Hey @Evansika Sure, you can definitely change the pad types. \nI do not understand what breaker cells are, but as long as the GND and VCC pads remain as laid out in the standard, you can still use the standard COB. \nIf you change any of those, that is alright as well, you will just have to design your own PBC. \nAn example of another person who has changed the PCB and all the pad types can be found in and around this post https://discord.com/channels/1361349522684510449/1429068742108909638/1429520076536811622\nLet me know if there have any more questions and I'll try to answer them.",
      "author": {
        "id": "756011607603019777",
